commit.message:
Add option to install tool man pages

Fix some strange redundant installation bug in the process.

Format meson.build files with muon

The less time wasted with manual code formatting, the better.
Replace strict option with new meson warning level
Fix clang and clang-tidy warnings on Windows
Fix and simplify library naming on Windows
Allow SORD_API to be defined by the user
Fix command line help interface of sord_validate

Add meson subproject files to .gitignore

This is generated in the source directory by meson when the project is checked
out of git by the meson wrap system.  Ignoring it here ignores issues with
tools that assume a clean source directory, like the REUSE test.

Use 0BSD for trivial "public domain intent" things

Fedora takes issue with CC0.  Although it doesn't really matter for this
stuff (dual licensed anyway, questionably "software", certainly not patentable,
and so on), this is simpler and more consistent with the ISC license used for
the actual software anyway.
Only run REUSE test in strict mode
Fix accidentally exposed internal zix symbols
